				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No. That is a different flag.<br /><br />When the IRQ happens, the IRQ flag bit in $4015 is set and will remain set until you read it. If the CPU is not masking IRQ signals (i.e. depending on the use of sei/cli instructions) the CPU will receive an IRQ signal while this bit is set.<br /><br />$4017's IRQ inhibit flag will prevent the operation of the IRQ flag bit in $4015, but reading $4015 does not set the IRQ inhibit flag in $4017.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

